title: "DICompileUnit not listed in llvm.dbg.cu" when building with "--emit asm"

body:
Repo: https://github.com/kivikakk/comrak

Commit: 4e95cea69b1b7083fbecfc55b9df90154d74f463

Toolchain: rustc 1.28.0-nightly (e3bf634e0 2018-06-28)

Error:

```
⟫ RUSTFLAGS="--emit asm" cargo +nightly build --release
    Updating registry `https://github.com/rust-lang/crates.io-index`
 Downloading typed-arena v1.4.1
   Compiling libc v0.2.42
   Compiling unicode-width v0.1.5
   Compiling lazy_static v1.0.1
   Compiling vec_map v0.8.1
   Compiling typed-arena v1.4.1
   Compiling textwrap v0.10.0
   Compiling thread_local v0.3.5
   Compiling memchr v2.0.1
   Compiling atty v0.2.10
   Compiling clap v2.32.0
   Compiling aho-corasick v0.6.5
   Compiling twoway v0.1.8
   Compiling regex v0.2.11
   Compiling comrak v0.2.13 (file:///home/brian/reddit/snoomark2)
DICompileUnit not listed in llvm.dbg.cu
!107218 = distinct !DICompileUnit(language: DW_LANG_Rust, file: !1774, producer: "clang LLVM (rustc version 1.28.0-nightly (e3bf634e0 2018-06-28))", isOptimized: true, runtimeVersion: 0, emissionKind: FullDebug, enums: !4)
LLVM ERROR: Broken module found, compilation aborted!
error: Could not compile `comrak`.

To learn more, run the command again with --verbose.
```

Also on 1.27.0
